{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/current-events-christmas/st-nicholas-day","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"St. Nicholas Day","meta_description":"St. Nicholas day Covid-19","content":{"processed":"<p><strong>Recommendations </strong></p>\n<p>\nSt. Nicholas, Angel and the Devil walk on the 5th of December every year. This tradition is very popular amongst parents and their children, at least amongst the naughty ones.</p>\n<p>However, in terms of the possible spread of the virus, this is a risky activity, and it is <strong>good to be cautious about it</strong>. There are <strong>no measures </strong>that would potentially affect St. Nicholas, respectively St. Nicholas events at the moment. </p>\n<p>However, the general measure on the restriction of the free movement of persons implies that <strong>only family members will be able to do the devil, St. Nicholas or the angel.</strong></p>\n<p>In case of a visit of the Devil, St. Nicholas and Angel at your home, it is recommended, if possible, that the <strong>meeting takes place outside</strong>.</p>\n<p>If it will be possible to hold social events with a St. Nicholas theme, please observe the general <strong>Wear Z </strong>(face masks - social distance - disinfect your hands) when participating in the events. This will prevent the virus from spreading and help protect yourself and your surroundings.<br />\n </p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/current-events-christmas/st-nicholas-day"},"valid_from":null,"links":[],"relationships":{"region":[],"icon":{"code":"child_care"},"situation_type":{"name":"CURRENT EVENTS: Christmas","path":{"alias":"/situations/current-events-christmas"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"calendar_today"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Measures on free movement","path":{"alias":"/situations/free-movement-people/measures-free-movement","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Meeting friends","path":{"alias":"/situations/childr